\f1\b 1. Voice/TTS for Audio Transcriptions on Interviews
\f0\b0 \
\
    
\f1\b What exists now:
\f0\b0  Telegram channel captures voice messages and saves .ogg files to data/channel_audio/. There is 
\f1\b no transcription
\f0\b0 \
    \'97 they just sit there as [voice message] placeholders.\
\
    
\f1\b What AgentScope has:
\f0\b0  VoiceAgent, RealtimeVoiceAgent, TTS module\
\
    
\f1\b How to implement in Istara's approach:
\f0\b0 \
     - 
\f1\b NOT
\f0\b0  real-time voice conversation (Istara is async, not a call center)\
     - 
\f1\b DO
\f0\b0  add Whisper/Ollama's native speech-to-text to the interview pipeline\
     - When a voice message arrives via Telegram/WhatsApp, automatically transcribe it using a local model (Whisper.cpp or Ollama's\
       speech capability)\
     - Store the transcription as interview text, link the original audio as an attachment\
     - Add a "Transcribe Audio" skill that batch-processes uploaded audio files from interviews\
     - This feeds directly into the Atomic Research chain: transcribed text \uc0\u8594  nuggets \u8594  facts \u8594  insights\
\
    
\f1\b Why this fits Istara:
\f0\b0  It's local-first (Whisper runs locally), it's domain-specific (interview transcription is core to UX\
    research), and it fills a real gap \'97 voice messages are captured but not processed.\
\
