\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 AgentScope explicitly avoids constraining models with heavy prompt templates. It delegates routing and planning to native LLM reasoning. This is elegant and works well when models are smart enough to self-direct.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b \cf0 \strokec2 Strength:
\f3\b0 \strokec2 \'a0Minimal framework overhead, leverages improving model capabilities naturally.\uc0\u8232 
\f4\b \strokec2 Weakness:
\f3\b0 \strokec2 \'a0Relies entirely on model quality \'97 when models hallucinate or make poor decisions, there\'92s no safety net.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa162\partightenfactor0

\fs32\fsmilli16250 \cf0 \strokec2 Istara: \'93Structure guides intelligence\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 Istara wraps every agent interaction in methodology: skill definitions with plan/execute prompts, evidence chains, self-verification, budget allocation, content guards. It assumes models need guardrails.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b \cf0 \strokec2 Strength:
\f3\b0 \strokec2 \'a0Consistent, methodology-driven outputs regardless of model quality. The Atomic Research chain ensures traceability.\uc0\u8232 
\f4\b \strokec2 Weakness:
\f3\b0 \strokec2 \'a0Heavier framework overhead. More code to maintain.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa195\partightenfactor0

